<title>USA: E-Z-EM Q3 March 31 net loss vs profit.</title>
<headline>E-Z-EM Q3 March 31 net loss vs profit.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>1997			1996</p>
<p> Shr loss	  $0.11	   profit $nil</p>
<p> Net loss	  1,046	   profit 9</p>
<p> Net sales	 23,576		   21,550</p>
<p> Avg shrs primary9,325		    9,768</p>
<p>	   9 MONTHS</p>
<p> Shr loss	  $0.03	   profit $2.16</p>
<p> Net  loss	 290	     profit 20,665</p>
<p> Net sales	 72,923		   66,554</p>
<p> Avg shrs primary9,289		    9,552</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTE: 9-month 1996 results include $2.03 per share gain from discontinued operations.</p>
<p>The company said poor results were mainly attributable to its Imaging Products unit.  Flat sales coupled with lower gross profits from unabsorbed overhead in its Canadian operation, as well as increased operating expenses, had a negative impact on results, the company said.</p>
<p>E-Z-EM Inc.</p>
